Frequently Asked Questions for RIT Capital Partners plc (LON:RCP)
What is RIT Capital Partners plc's stock symbol?

RIT Capital Partners plc trades on the London Stock Exchange (LON) under the ticker symbol "RCP."



How often does RIT Capital Partners plc pay dividends? What is the dividend yield for RIT Capital Partners plc?

RIT Capital Partners plc announced a  dividend on Tuesday, February 28th. Stockholders of record on Thursday, April 6th will be paid a dividend of GBX 16 per share on Friday, April 28th. This represents a dividend yield of 0.85%. The ex-dividend date of this dividend is Thursday, April 6th. This is an increase from RIT Capital Partners plc's previous  dividend of $15.50. The official announcement can be viewed at this link.  View RIT Capital Partners plc's Dividend History.



When will RIT Capital Partners plc make its next earnings announcement?

RIT Capital Partners plc is scheduled to release their next quarterly earnings announcement on Tuesday, August, 15th 2017. View Earnings Estimates for RIT Capital Partners plc.



Who are some of RIT Capital Partners plc's key competitors?

 Some companies that are related to RIT Capital Partners plc include Compass Diversified Holdings (CODI), Capital Southwest Corporation (CSWC), Draper Esprit PLC (GROW), Tiziana Life Sciences PLC (TILS), CM Finance (CMFN), Saratoga Investment Corp (SAR), Gresham House plc (GHE), Cluff Natural Resources PLC (CLNR), Amedeo Resources PLC (AMED), Legendary Investments plc (LEG), Amedeo Resources PLC (CRO), Greencoat UK Wind PLC (UKW), Henderson Global Trust PLC (HGL), International Biotechnology Trust Plc (IBT), iShares S&P NA Tec. Semi. Idx. Fd.(ETF) (SOXX), Standard Life Equity Income Trust Plc (SLET) and Tiziana Life Sciences PLC (ADI).



Who are RIT Capital Partners plc's key executives?

RIT Capital Partners plc's management team includes the folowing people: Jacob Rothschild, Executive Chairman of the BoardBaroness Ariane De Rothschild, Honorary Vice Chairman of the BoardJean Laurent-Bellue, Non-Executive Non-Independent DirectorHannah Mary Rothschild, Non-Executive Non-Independent DirectorJohn E. Cornish, Non-Executive Independent DirectorMichael Marks, Senior Independent Non-Executive Director



How do I buy RIT Capital Partners plc stock? 

Shares of RIT Capital Partners plc and other U.K. stocks can be purchased through online brokerage accounts that support trading on the London Stock Exchange (LSX). Some U.K. companies can be purchased through major U.S. brokerages in the form of American Depository Receipts (ADRs), which are placeholder equities held in a trust by a bank that represent shares of a foreign stock.



What is RIT Capital Partners plc's stock price today?

One share of RIT Capital Partners plc stock can currently be purchased for approximately GBX 1,939.


